To ensure users with "Can Edit" permissions cannot extend others' permissions beyond their own expiration date.
h4. Scenario Overview:
 * Folder Structure: FolderA/FolderB/FolderC
 ** Andy has "Can Edit" permission for FolderC, expiring on 10/31.
 ** Irene has "Can View" permission for FolderB, inherited by FolderC, expiring on 11/30.
 * Action Trigger: Andy attempts to change Irene’s permission for FolderC from "Can View" to "Can Edit."
 * Conflict: Andy’s permission expires on 10/31, while Irene’s permission (inherited) expires on 11/30.

h4. Resolution Mechanism:
 * A system warning is shown to Andy, informing him that changes will reduce Irene’s permission expiration to match his own (10/31).
 * Andy can either proceed or cancel the changes.

h4. Dialog Title & Content:
{code:java}
@Permission Expiration Conflict@

@The changes you are attempting will affect the selected user permission expiration date. You cannot set an expiration date beyond your own expiration date ({current_qid_xdate}). Do you want to continue with the changes or cancel?@
@Continue@
@Cancel@
{code}

